<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="140" pageId="3" pageNumber="139" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1801,2008]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,825]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="140" pageId="3" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,325,1801,1827]" pageId="3" pageNumber="139">Redescription.</emphasis>
Body mid-size (
<quantity box="[506,633,1801,1828]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="139" unit="mm" value="30.0" valueMax="35.0" valueMin="25.0">25–35 mm</quantity>
.), body surface generally smooth and shiny, color reddish (
<figureCitation box="[1278,1354,1801,1828]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1948,1972]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,415,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-89@2.[151,1436,414,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cratomelus armatus male habitus. A. Lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Head and thorax in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919888/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="139">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[1406,1423,1802,1828]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,525,1942]" captionTargetId="figure-206@6.[151,1436,525,1943]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Cratomelus armatus female habitus. A. Lateral and B. Dorsal views respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919896" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919896/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="139">4</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,215,1838,1864]" pageId="3" pageNumber="139">Head</emphasis>
as broad as pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[474,561,1837,1864]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1948,1972]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,415,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-89@2.[151,1436,414,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cratomelus armatus male habitus. A. Lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Head and thorax in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919888/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
), rounded and smooth; almost as wide as high in frontal view (
<figureCitation box="[1257,1344,1837,1864]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1948,1972]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,415,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-89@2.[151,1436,414,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cratomelus armatus male habitus. A. Lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Head and thorax in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919888/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Vertex rounded. Eyes ovoid, not protruding. Ocelli circular and small. The eyes and antennal pits are located in the middle of the face (
<figureCitation box="[286,374,1909,1936]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1948,1972]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,415,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-89@2.[151,1436,414,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cratomelus armatus male habitus. A. Lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Head and thorax in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919888/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Fastigium moderately narrow, almost as wide as the scape, lateral edges sulcated. Mandibles of the male without sexual specialization. Maxillary palpi longer, first and second subequal in size and rectangular; third cylindrical almost two times longer as the first and second together; fourth as long as the third, five little longer than the fourth with the apex with a small prolongation (
<figureCitation box="[774,862,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1948,1972]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,415,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-89@2.[151,1436,414,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cratomelus armatus male habitus. A. Lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Head and thorax in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919888/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[882,978,151,177]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Thorax.</emphasis>
Pronotal disc longer than wide; posterior margin rounded and little broader than the anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[808,895,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1948,1972]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,415,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-89@2.[151,1436,414,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cratomelus armatus male habitus. A. Lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Head and thorax in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919888/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
); lateral lobules rectangular, wider than high and with a rounded lateral edge, ventral margin almost straight (
<figureCitation box="[811,906,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1948,1972]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,415,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-89@2.[151,1436,414,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cratomelus armatus male habitus. A. Lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Head and thorax in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919888/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Figs. 1A</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[958,996,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,525,1942]" captionTargetId="figure-206@6.[151,1436,525,1943]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Cratomelus armatus female habitus. A. Lateral and B. Dorsal views respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919896" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919896/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">4A</figureCitation>
). Meso and metanotum unmodified and without glandular pits. Prosternum armed with a pair of closely spaced triangular spines; mesosternum quadrangular with rounded lateral lobes and a notch in the middle of the lobes; metasternum hexagonal, 3.5 times wider than long, with a small notch on the posterior margin. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[710,786,330,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Wings</emphasis>
shortened, with distinctly S-shaped CuP and the widened area between MP+CuA2 (
<figureCitation box="[444,537,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1623,1647]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[151,1437,181,1599]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cratomelus armatus male. A. Fore and B. Middle legs. C. hind femur. D and E. Hind tibia in lateral and dorsal view. F. Tegmina. G. Hind wing. H–K. Terminalia in dorsal, axial, lateral and ventral view respectively. L. paraproct and cerci. (The red arrows in figures F and G, show the wing veins modification. The white arrow in figure I, show the hook of the last tergite)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919892/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Figs. 2F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[549,587,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,525,1942]" captionTargetId="figure-206@6.[151,1436,525,1943]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Cratomelus armatus female habitus. A. Lateral and B. Dorsal views respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919896" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919896/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">4A</figureCitation>
); hind wings in both sexes transformed into stridulatory apparatus (tegmino alar stridulation) (
<figureCitation box="[358,461,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1623,1647]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[151,1437,181,1599]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cratomelus armatus male. A. Fore and B. Middle legs. C. hind femur. D and E. Hind tibia in lateral and dorsal view. F. Tegmina. G. Hind wing. H–K. Terminalia in dorsal, axial, lateral and ventral view respectively. L. paraproct and cerci. (The red arrows in figures F and G, show the wing veins modification. The white arrow in figure I, show the hook of the last tergite)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919892/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Figs. 2G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[476,512,402,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[227,1362,185,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-28@7.[225,1362,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Cratomelus armatus female. A. Tegmina. B. Hind wing. C. Terminalia axial view. D. Subgenital plate. E. Terminalia lateral view. (The white arrows in figures A and B, show the wing veins modification)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919902/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">5B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[535,598,403,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Legs.</emphasis>
Coxae laterally flattened, with a distal spine on the dorsal margin. Fore and mid femora with few small spines on ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[821,889,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1623,1647]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[151,1437,181,1599]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cratomelus armatus male. A. Fore and B. Middle legs. C. hind femur. D and E. Hind tibia in lateral and dorsal view. F. Tegmina. G. Hind wing. H–K. Terminalia in dorsal, axial, lateral and ventral view respectively. L. paraproct and cerci. (The red arrows in figures F and G, show the wing veins modification. The white arrow in figure I, show the hook of the last tergite)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919892/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
A-B, hind femur slightly serrulate ventrally and dorsally and without rows on inner side; outer side with well-developed chevrons relief (
<figureCitation box="[1131,1219,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1623,1647]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[151,1437,181,1599]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cratomelus armatus male. A. Fore and B. Middle legs. C. hind femur. D and E. Hind tibia in lateral and dorsal view. F. Tegmina. G. Hind wing. H–K. Terminalia in dorsal, axial, lateral and ventral view respectively. L. paraproct and cerci. (The red arrows in figures F and G, show the wing veins modification. The white arrow in figure I, show the hook of the last tergite)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919892/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Fore tibia without tympana (
<figureCitation box="[263,353,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1623,1647]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[151,1437,181,1599]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cratomelus armatus male. A. Fore and B. Middle legs. C. hind femur. D and E. Hind tibia in lateral and dorsal view. F. Tegmina. G. Hind wing. H–K. Terminalia in dorsal, axial, lateral and ventral view respectively. L. paraproct and cerci. (The red arrows in figures F and G, show the wing veins modification. The white arrow in figure I, show the hook of the last tergite)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919892/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); fore and mid tibiae with movable spurs on ventral margins, apex, and two or one dorsally spurs (
<figureCitation box="[159,298,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1623,1647]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[151,1437,181,1599]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cratomelus armatus male. A. Fore and B. Middle legs. C. hind femur. D and E. Hind tibia in lateral and dorsal view. F. Tegmina. G. Hind wing. H–K. Terminalia in dorsal, axial, lateral and ventral view respectively. L. paraproct and cerci. (The red arrows in figures F and G, show the wing veins modification. The white arrow in figure I, show the hook of the last tergite)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919892/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Figs. 2A–B</figureCitation>
). Hind tibiae with strong and not movable dorsal spines, the apex spurs movable and conspicuous (
<figureCitation box="[159,293,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1623,1647]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[151,1437,181,1599]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cratomelus armatus male. A. Fore and B. Middle legs. C. hind femur. D and E. Hind tibia in lateral and dorsal view. F. Tegmina. G. Hind wing. H–K. Terminalia in dorsal, axial, lateral and ventral view respectively. L. paraproct and cerci. (The red arrows in figures F and G, show the wing veins modification. The white arrow in figure I, show the hook of the last tergite)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919892/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Figs. 2D–E</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[310,427,582,608]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Abdomen</emphasis>
cylindrical, penultimate tergite of male varying, prolonged or not; medial parts of ultimate tergite not separated from its lateral parts, with hooks (
<figureCitation box="[779,860,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1623,1647]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[151,1437,181,1599]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cratomelus armatus male. A. Fore and B. Middle legs. C. hind femur. D and E. Hind tibia in lateral and dorsal view. F. Tegmina. G. Hind wing. H–K. Terminalia in dorsal, axial, lateral and ventral view respectively. L. paraproct and cerci. (The red arrows in figures F and G, show the wing veins modification. The white arrow in figure I, show the hook of the last tergite)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919892/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Fig. 2I</figureCitation>
). Paraprocts wide, curved, and flattened (
<figureCitation box="[1335,1424,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1623,1647]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[151,1437,181,1599]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cratomelus armatus male. A. Fore and B. Middle legs. C. hind femur. D and E. Hind tibia in lateral and dorsal view. F. Tegmina. G. Hind wing. H–K. Terminalia in dorsal, axial, lateral and ventral view respectively. L. paraproct and cerci. (The red arrows in figures F and G, show the wing veins modification. The white arrow in figure I, show the hook of the last tergite)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919892/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Fig. 2L</figureCitation>
). Male subgenital plates with articulated styles (
<figureCitation box="[689,782,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1623,1647]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[151,1437,181,1599]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cratomelus armatus male. A. Fore and B. Middle legs. C. hind femur. D and E. Hind tibia in lateral and dorsal view. F. Tegmina. G. Hind wing. H–K. Terminalia in dorsal, axial, lateral and ventral view respectively. L. paraproct and cerci. (The red arrows in figures F and G, show the wing veins modification. The white arrow in figure I, show the hook of the last tergite)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919892/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Fig. 2K</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[805,985,654,681]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Small, almost entirely membranous, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1419,1436,654,680]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">ti</emphasis>
moderately sclerotized, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[427,489,691,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">lw.vl.</emphasis>
with microstructures (
<figureCitation box="[753,825,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1851,1875]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1827]" captionTargetId="figure-28@5.[151,1435,181,1827]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Cratomelus armatus male genitalia. A. Dorsal. B. Ventral. C. Axial and D. Inside views respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919894" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919894/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[850,945,691,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Female.</emphasis>
Similar to male (
<figureCitation box="[1154,1227,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,525,1942]" captionTargetId="figure-206@6.[151,1436,525,1943]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Cratomelus armatus female habitus. A. Lateral and B. Dorsal views respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919896" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919896/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate triangular (
<figureCitation box="[275,365,726,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[227,1362,185,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-28@7.[225,1362,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Cratomelus armatus female. A. Tegmina. B. Hind wing. C. Terminalia axial view. D. Subgenital plate. E. Terminalia lateral view. (The white arrows in figures A and B, show the wing veins modification)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919902/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
), ovipositor mid-sized, tapering towards apex, and moderately curved (
<figureCitation box="[1163,1250,726,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[227,1362,185,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-28@7.[225,1362,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Cratomelus armatus female. A. Tegmina. B. Hind wing. C. Terminalia axial view. D. Subgenital plate. E. Terminalia lateral view. (The white arrows in figures A and B, show the wing veins modification)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919902/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Fig. 5E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
